<div class="section" id="departments">
<h2>Departments</h2>
<div class="departments">
<ul>
<li><strong>Chemical Engineering</strong>:The Department of Chemical Engineering started its meritorious journey in 2013, 
with the objective of moulding young minds with outstanding excellence in the field of Chemical Engineering and Technology.</li>
<li><strong>Civil Engineering:</strong>The Dept. is also privileged to have an extremely dynamic and dedicated faculty whose expertise has been widely acknowledged. 
Civil engineers build the worldâ€™s infrastructure, which enables them to have opportunities galore with new players entering the market and large- scale developments announced around the globe.
</li>
<li><strong>Computer Science & Engineering:</strong>The Dept of Computer Science and Engineering is one of the best units that has always enhanced the glory of AJCE.</li>
<li><strong>Food Technology:</strong>Food processing industry is very vast and versatile, and it provides promising career opportunities to the young generation.</li>
<li><strong>Electronics & Communication Engineering:</strong>The Department of Electronics and Communication Engineering started its commendable journey in 2001. With excellent infrastructure and full- fledged faculty, 
the department has always been in the path of rapid progress, making it one of the premier departments of Amal Jyothi</strong></li>
<li><strong>Electrical & Electronics Engineering:</strong>The Department of Electrical and Electronics Engineering was established in 2001. 
Postgraduate courses in Power Electronics and Power Systems were introduced in 2009, followed by Energy Systems in 2013.</li>
<li><strong>Mechanical Engineering:</strong>The Department of Mechanical Engineering began its remarkable journey in 2004 and has been committed to excellence ever since. With a focus on shaping skilled and dedicated professionals,
we uphold the highest standards in education while fostering academic and technical excellence among our students.</li>
<li><strong>Metallurgical & Materials Engineering:</strong>Metallurgical and Materials Engineering break through the bottleneck, between today's challenges and tomorrow's solutions.</li>
</ul>
